       An MWM resource description file is a standard text file
       containing items of information separated by blanks, tabs,    |
       and newline characters.  Blank lines are ignored.  Items or
       characters can be quoted to avoid special interpretation      |
       (for example, the comment character can be quoted to prevent  |
       it from being interpreted as the comment character).  A       |
       quoted item can be contained in " (double quotation marks).   |
       Single characters can be quoted by preceding them with        |
       \ (the backslash character).  All text from an unquoted #     |
       (comment) character to the end of the line is regarded as a
       comment and is not interpreted as part of a resource
       description.  If an ! (exclamation poin) is the first char-   |
       acter of a line, the line is regarded as a comment.

